{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐκλύω</b> [ῡ, <br /> see at {λύω}], <b>set free,</b> πόνων <b>from</b> labours, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 328 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>release,</b> ὕδατα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PTeb.” 49.6 (2nd c.BC)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be set free,</b> ἐκλέλυμαι πόθου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 1339; ἐκ δεσμῶν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 67d \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, <b>get</b> one <b>set free, release,</b> ἀλλ᾽ ἄγε δή σε κακῶν ἐκλύσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.286; τοῦ φόβου σ᾽ ἐξελυσάμην 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1003; θανάτου νιν ἐκλύσασθε 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 818; ἐξελυσάμην βροτοὺς τὸ μὴ μολεῖν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 237: with _accusative_ _person_ only, ἐξελύσαντο τοὺς Ἀργείους 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 7.1.25: _absolutely_, ἐξελυσάμην\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] I <b>delivered</b> him <b>from danger,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 531. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>unloose,</b> ἐ. τόξα <b>unstring</b> a bow, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.173; ἐ. ἁρμούς 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 825 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σκαιὸν ἐκλύσων στόμα <b>likely to let loose</b> a foolish tongue, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1225. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>make an end of,</b> ἐξέλυσας..σκληρᾶς ἀοιδοῦ δασμόν <b>paid</b> it <b>off,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “OT” 35; ἐπίπονον ἁμέραν [prev. author] “Tr.” 654; μόχθον 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 695; ἔριν καὶ φιλονικίαν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 9.14 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐξελύσατε (variant{-λύσασθε}) τὰς παρασκευάς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 18.26. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>relax,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 610a27; τῆς φροντίδος τὸ ἀκριβές 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Dom.” 17 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:— <i>passive</i>, <b>to be faint, fail,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἀφορισμοί” 2.41, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 15.59, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.224, 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Ir.” p.69 W., etc.; πρὸς τὸν πόλεμον 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 4.150 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐκλυθῆναι τοῖς σώμασι, τῇ ψυχῇ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Fragmenta” 144, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 29.17.4 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] (so <i>intransitive</i> in <i>active</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Bellum Judaicum” 1.33.5)\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>], etc.; of things, <b>to be unserviceable,</b> τὰ τῶν πλοίων ἐκλελυμένα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1320b37 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἐκλύεται ὁ ῥοῦς, τὰ ῥεύματα, <b>cease,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 4.43.9, 4.41.5. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> in Medicine texts, ἐ. κοιλίαν <b>relax</b> the bowels, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 4.169. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> <b>pay in full,</b> δάνειον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Caesar” 12 (_passive_). \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.5.b</b></Level4> <b>purchase,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 6.91. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.6</b></Level3> <b>resolve</b> a doubt, in <i>passive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Syntaxi;” 176.24; also τὰ ὑπ᾽ ἀμφιβολίαν πίπτοντα ἐκλύεται τοῦ ἀμφιβόλου [prev. work] 311.11. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.7</b></Level3> <b>dissolve,</b> τι ὄξει [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 11.106. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>intransitive</i>, <b>to break up, depart,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.2Mac.13.16. \">LXX</a>]","strongNumber":"G1590","accentedUnicode":"ἐκλύω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0413","matchingForm":"ἀνέκλειπτος","stepTransliteration":"anekleiptos","gloss":"inexhaustible","_zh_tw_Gloss":"用不盡","_es_Gloss":"inagotable","_zh_Gloss":"用不尽"},{"strongNumber":"G1537","matchingForm":"ἐκ","stepTransliteration":"ek","gloss":"out from","_zh_tw_Gloss":"從","_es_Gloss":"de ","_zh_Gloss":"从"},{"strongNumber":"G1587","matchingForm":"ἐκλείπω","stepTransliteration":"ekleipō","gloss":"to fail","_zh_tw_Gloss":"窮盡, 錢財無用","_es_Gloss":"fallar ","_zh_Gloss":"穷尽, 钱财无用"},{"strongNumber":"G3089","matchingForm":"λύω","stepTransliteration":"luō","gloss":"to loose","_zh_tw_Gloss":"解","_es_Gloss":"soltar","_zh_Gloss":"解"}],"shortDef":"(<i>passive</i>) to faint","mediumDef":"(<i>passive</i>) to faint <br /><b>to be weary, exhausted, faint,lose heart; give up; collapse in weariness; </b>,</b> <ref='Mat.15.32'>Mt. 15:32</ref>; <ref='Mrk.8.3'>Mk. 8:3</ref>; <ref='Gal.6.9'>Gal. 6:9;</ref> <b>to lose courage, to faint,</b> <ref='Heb.12.3'>Heb. 12:3</ref>, 5*","stepGloss":"to faint","stepTransliteration":"ekluō","count":5,"_es_Definition":"renunciar, rendirse ; desmayar, desfallecer","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) (字意) 由...解脫<br>2) 疲憊, 筋疲力竭","_zh_Definition":"1) (字意) 由...解脱<br>2) 疲惫, 筋疲力竭","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"khốn đốn; khốn cùng; thiếu sức mạnh; mất can đảm. ἐκ (G1537) + 